    "R Studio version 4.33 (2024.04+735, Posit Software, PBC) (within the R programming language) was employed as the instrument for all data analysis.",
    "R is a comprehensive programming environment encompassing complex natural language processing, statistical data analysis, data visualisation, and the creation of applications and websites (Schweinberger 2023; Verzani 2011).",
    "Before importing the data into R Studio, the reference list from each text was manually removed and the file format was converted from \"doc.\" to \"txt.\"",
    "In R Studio, several essential data analysis packages were installed, including 'here ', 'stringr', 'dplyr', 'ggplot2', 'quanteda', 'quanteda.textstats', 'tm (Text mining) ' to process and promote the textual data with loading, searching, cleaning, annotating, and visualizing within a single tool (Arnold et al. 2019).",
    "Subsequently, the command 'library' was used to activate all analysis packages."
